INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (222001, 'Draft ThreeBecause I never realized that you could fall in love with humans the same way you fall in love with songs. How the tune of them could mean nothing to you at first, an unfamiliar melody, but quickly turn into a symphony carved across your skin; a hymn in the web of your veins; a harmony stitched into the lining of your soul', 4945, 0), (222002, 'You''re not who I thought you''d be, Cas." "No?" "Your so much better.', 8091, 0), (222003, 'I can taste the good-bye on his lips.', 237, 0), (222004, 'Because I never realized that you could fall in love with humans the same way you fall in love with songs. How the tune of them could mean nothing to you at first, an unfamiliar melody, but quickly turn into a symphony carved across your skin; a hymn in the web of your veins; a harmony stitched into the lining of your soul.', 4945, 0), (222005, 'After you leftI stared at the drivewayFeeling its emptinessWondering if you’d return.After you leftI thought about your questionsWishing I hadn’t been so bluntWondering if I scared you away.After you leftI remembered how you felt in my arms.How you fit so perfectly there. Like my guitar.Wondering if I should have kissed you when I had the chance.After you leftI sat in my roomRemembering all the things you said, andWondering about all the things you didn’t.After you leftI sat in silence.Missing you in a way I didn’t quite understand.Wondering if you’d ever come back.', 31455, 0), (222006, 'They were just so different, and she kept wondering if he''d realize this was a mistake at some point; if, once she stopped being the novelty, the random American, he would recognize who she really was -- a nerdy bookworm, a happy loner -- and move on.', 309, 0), (222007, '...and it struck her as the truest form of kindness, the most basic sort of love: to be worried about the one who was worrying about you.', 309, 0), (222008, 'Because even this --being so close to her --was no longer the same. That light he''d felt when he first saw her --he understood now that it was only a lightbulb. It was quick and easy, full of electricity, but there was something artificial about it. What he wanted was fire: heat and spark and flame.', 309, 0), (222009, 'I love you too much to lose you over something so little.  “Roommates With Benefits.', 3333, 0), (222010, 'Just because you painted a house didn''t mean the furniture inside was any different. It had to be the same with people.', 309, 0), (222011, 'May your eye go to the Sun, To the wind your soul... You are all the colors in one, at full brightness.', 419, 0), (222012, 'Someone like you is brilliant and amazing.'' I said. ''Why can''t you see that in yourself?'' The unfairness of it was starting to sink in. If she could only see herself like I did, there wouldn''t be a problem. But she didn''t, and she never would, and that was so many levels of wrong and unfair I almost couldn''t comprehend it.', 14682, 0), (222013, 'People in pain can be very self-destructive. And sometimes they pull in the people who are close to them, often without realizing.', 14682, 0), (222014, 'It''s me, asking him to let me in. Asking all of them to give a chance to show them that, deep down, I''m not who they think I am. Or, maybe I''m exactly who they think I am, but I no longer want to be.', 31455, 0), (222015, 'Actually, judging by Pinterest alone, I''m pretty sure a lot of people would look forward to hanging out in such a beautiful library. Just not people Peter knows. He thinks I''m so quirky. I''m not planning on being the one to break the news to him that I''m actually not that quirky, that in fact lots of people like to stay home and bake cookies and scrapbook and hang out in libraries. Most of them are probably in their fifties, but still. I like the way he looks at me, like I am a wood nymph that he happened upon one day and just had to take home to keep.', 214, 0), (222016, 'I am made of a thousand ghosts. Only you can shoot me down.', 16879, 0), (222017, 'Perhaps death is just a big lie.', 16879, 0), (222018, 'Because when I kiss you, I want yours to be the first... and last lips I ever kiss.', 333, 0), (222019, 'I-" Irsa took a careful breath to steady her words. " I have felt alone for most of my life. Until you." She placed the shell on his chest. " But I promise I won''t feel alone anymore. I will never forget." She stood on shaky feet. "I will always remember." "I love you Rahim al-Din Walad . Thank you for loving me in return.', 333, 0), (222020, 'Khalid would break every bone in your body for what you''ve done.', 333, 0), (222021, 'You deserve someone who will feel you at her side without needing to see you. And I''ve only felt that way about one boy.', 333, 0), (222022, 'I knew I was not alone. They would never leave until ever last one of us was gone.', 39615, 0), (222023, 'I tapped my cup to his, grateful to have found Shaun, because for a minute there, I''d thought I was going to have to save myself. Instead, I''d wandered into the protective care of a sexy older man.', 155, 0), (222024, 'Funny story. A bunch of people -- the cult -- blame the appearance of abilities on the invention of the internet.', 39616, 0), (222025, 'Celerity: noun, mass noun; an ability possessed by certain Que Cum Virtute Judicium (Virts) increasing the mobility or swiftness of movement', 39616, 0), (222026, 'But just being whatever it is that I am . . . I don’t think that makes me a monster. Believe me, I know. ere are plenty of real monsters walking around out there in the world. ey look respectable, but can’t hide who they are from me. Real monsters hurt people for pleasure, or for no reason at all—they’re just not as well armed as I am.', 39617, 0), (222027, 'You see the world for what it is and what it could be,” Jack says. “What you don’t see is the gaping chasm in between … and that’s what I found.', 7556, 0), (222028, 'To describe a kiss is to describe a diary entry or a pair of underwear—each is personal and private, slightly awkward. Very awkward. But necessary.', 7556, 0), (222029, 'She trailed behind Baba and Jiji as they left the palace, nightingales singing a sad farewell.', 39618, 0), (222030, 'This was her heritage. Her people. So why did she feel so small and weak? So far removed from it?', 39618, 0), (222031, 'I look up and watch the bad parts of me shrinking to dots in the wide blue.', 39619, 0), (222032, 'The problem with playing hide-and-seek with your sister is that sometimes she gets bored and stops looking for you.And there you are - under the couch, in the closet, wedged behind the lilac tree - and you don''t want to give up, because maybe she''s just biding her time. But maybe she''s wandered off...', 54, 0), (222033, 'You''re such a dork.But I''m your dork.', 39620, 0), (222034, 'Parents aren''t supposed to cry. Or get scared. Or lie. Right? I thought I knew all the rules. But there are no rules.', 15800, 0), (222035, 'And if he was kind and friendly and funny, and if he told you about places so beautiful that you wanted to go with him to see them, and if he listened to you talk like he actually cared about what you were saying? And if he tried to protect you when other people tried to tell you what to do, as if they owned you? And if he has the handsomest face you''ve ever seen, no matter if the skin has been damaged, because he''s just lovely even so?', 7583, 0), (222036, 'And prayer? How could you pray to a God you wanted to hit?', 186, 0), (222037, 'Be selfish sometimes. Love yourself. If you always put others before you, you will find yourself feeling beaten down by the world and that will make you bitter. Don’t let the world make you bitter, not when you have such a beautiful soul.', 39621, 0), (222038, 'A Time Comes When Silence is Betrayal.', 35949, 0), (222039, 'Thunderbird ascended on the heady currents of air that bore her high above the vast landscape of Túwaqachi. She stretched her broad wings, the heat lifting her through the silence, her glossy brown feathers shimmering in the sunlight.', 35949, 0), (222040, 'The early morning sunshine shot up the ice-covered valley. It glinted off the backs of slumbering mastodon, reflected between the antlers of caribou.', 35949, 0), (222041, 'For whom do you cry, my son?” the Great Spirit asked.“I do not know.”“Yes, you do.', 35949, 0), (222042, 'This is a time of change,” the Shaman said. “This is a time of enormous power.', 35949, 0), (222043, 'We must treat with respect our world and all upon it. Túwaqachi is not inherited from our ancestors', 39622, 0), (222044, 'Do you understand the meaning of the soil beneath your feet?', 35949, 0), (222045, 'The Sun Dagger appeared on the rock face directly above the Shaman’s shadowed head. It dazzled within the shade as the sunlight slipped through a gap in the overhead slabs. The dagger cut slowly down the rock, slicing through the very center of the etched spiral. “The middle of time,” Chaco whispered to himself.', 35949, 0), (222046, 'The other Clans will soon arrive. The greatest times of our family are before us. And so are the darkest.', 35949, 0), (222047, 'One large cat bounded up the side of the outcrop to stand in full view on an overhanging boulder. She stared down at them, inside their protective enclosure, tilting her head from side to side. Her scarred yellow-brown coat was immaculately groomed, but the long tufting hair of her snout was matted with the bright red smear of uncongealed blood from a recent kill. Her upper lip curved over the top of foot-long saber teeth.', 35949, 0), (222048, 'We the People . . . The People of the Long House.', 35949, 0), (222049, 'The Day of Trouble is Near', 35949, 0), (222050, 'We must love our slaves, Papa. We must love them as hard as we are able.', 35949, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (222051, 'West Point—The Key to the Continent and Independence.', 35949, 0), (222052, 'No words in our ledgers could do justice to this sublime beauty,” Captain Lewis said. “The expedition should have brought a camera obscura.”Peter wasn’t familiar with the words, but no matter. He knew he was part of something magnificent—something greater than himself or the Corps of Discovery. And he knew what it was. It was America. And it was beautiful.', 35949, 0), (222053, 'I refuse to believe the people of Texas and all Americans in the world have forgotten us.', 35949, 0), (222054, 'Do not fret, my brother, my child. For the buffalo will roam the plains once more.', 35949, 0), (222055, 'We live in a complicated society, Bromley—one that is changing and which does indeed need to change. But do you not think any change must begin within our own family gathering?', 35949, 0), (222056, 'Rainbow Cloud strode forward like a hunting cat with the same strength of height and broad shoulders, the same rolling gait as First Light’s father. They were indeed the same man, split in two at birth, so the family might be rewarded by twice the skill in hunting each brother possessed.', 35949, 0), (222057, 'The Sleepin’ Fox Catches No Poultry.', 35949, 0), (222058, 'A scratching of melody comes from the radio, chords rising open as the land that carries us, rhythm mimicking our passage down the road, harmony making this life seem it should be only that. We sing along to what songs have always been about- beginning, going on, breaking up, forgiving, We sing in missed words and broken phrases as glints of tiger moths fly at us like snow, streaking the windshield over.', 37067, 0), (222059, 'There were no stars, only the darkness and an arctic chill that had intensified since the first thin, blood-red stripes of sunrise shimmered on the ocean’s horizon.', 35949, 0), (222060, 'You are the monster I claim, mein Herr.', 7592, 0), (222061, 'Cameron, my heart is quite literally in this,', 3246, 0), (222062, 'There are good days and hard days for me. Don''t let the hard days win ~Mor ~A Court of Mist and Fury', 343, 0), (222063, '..they were always asking me lots of questions. Questions I didn''t want to answer. They wanted to get to know me. Yeah, well, I wasn''t interested in being known. I wanted to buy a t-shirt that read: I AM UNKNOWNABLE.', 186, 0), (222064, 'His hands still on his shoulders. “Hi,” he says. “Sorry.” “For what?” “For the fact that you are such a big flirt.” He laughs. “You’re the one in my lap. I was just sitting here minding my own business.” “Just the plane, then?” “Of course.” I try to stand up, but he pulls me back down again. “Man, the plane is really bumpy today,” he says.', 2355, 0), (222065, 'Some human beings in their craftiness thought they can pretend to be good when they are actually bad.', 7533, 0), (222066, 'Who am I kidding? This isn’t a fairy tale. It’s my life.', 12625, 0), (222067, 'Hearsay, even from the people I love, doesn''t equate to gospel truth.', 345, 0), (222068, 'Have you thought of doing it? Being a cattle farmer? If that''s what it''s called? I think we should do that, but replace cattle with bunnies and then we don''t milk or eat the bunnies. We just let them multiply. Then we''ll take over the world. Me the queen. You the king. Our bunnies the army nobody can defeat.', 345, 0), (222069, 'We were perfectly placed, perfectly disposed to one another. Our pieces fit so well together, not in the way that puzzle pieces are carved to click, but in a clumsier, more accidental way; we were a city skyline – unplanned architectural mastery. Designed by the heavens, and you called me your angel – even when I was undeserving of that accolade. You’d call yourself the devil and I’d feel betrayed. Because for me, we were the same, either two sinners or two saints.', 39491, 0), (222070, 'You and I have been friends long enough to know how to treat each other . . . I''m leaving for college. I think I''ve outgrown the rules.', 39623, 0), (222071, 'They lived and they laughed and they saw it was good.', 7757, 0), (222072, 'I DON’T KNOW! I HAVE NO FREAKIN’ IDEA. I’M ONLY FIFTEEN. I want my mom.', 12636, 0), (222073, 'That''s when I realized the chill wasn''t coming from outside—it was coming from within me.', 1474, 0), (222074, 'But you’re right about one thing: he’s my best friend. I know him very well, and no matter what he said or did tonight, I’ve never seen him act this way with another girl. No one,” he repeated, “except you.', 15751, 0), (222075, 'It is now my favorite book of all time, but then again, I always think that until I read another book.', 6, 0), (222076, 'The sun had begun its descent toward the horizon, and the sounds of the carnival played like a familiar song behind me.', 1474, 0), (222077, 'Darkness engulfed me...There was no ground below me, no sky above. Only the black, and the cold.', 1474, 0), (222078, 'Marika was a book nerd and had a TBR pile taller than her. She was a sucker for YA', 15751, 0), (222079, 'Love is more than blind. It''s brain-dead.', 431, 0), (222080, 'He looked at me then, his deep golden eyes meeting mine, and I saw a heat in them that I felt reflecting in my own.', 1474, 0), (222081, 'I think music is seasonal. In the summer my taste changes.', 412, 0), (222082, 'Are you here for a reason, Cheshire?Why, yes, I would enjoy a cup of tea. I take mine with lots of cream, and no tea. Thank you.', 302, 0), (222083, 'Courage does not take over, it fights and struggles through every word you say and every step you take. It''s a battle or a dance as to whether you let it pervade. It takes courage to overcome, but it takes extreme fear to be courageous.', 413, 0), (222084, 'Plus, how can she be your soul mate? Didn''t you tell me she''d never read Harry Potter? Do you really want to spend the rest of your life with someone like that? I mean, for God''s sake, think of your children. What kind of environment would they be growing up in with such a mother?', 4945, 0), (222085, 'The question stayed with me every day, through every class, through every Op. I felt its teeth tighten around the back of my neck each time I was dismissed without a second look; it had locked it’s jaws and wouldn’t let me or my conscience go.', 568, 0), (222086, 'The trouble was, I did know what I wanted from Grace Towne. I wanted to sleep with her, sure. I wanted her to be my girlfriend. A few years from now, I wanted to marry her. And then, when we were old, I wanted to drink peppermint tea and read Harry Potter to our grandchildren with her on the veranda of an old house out in the countryside as we watched a summer storm roll toward us. Was that so much to ask?', 4945, 0), (222087, 'Well, looks like you got your wish, Firebrand," I whispered, feeling the heat in my veins rise up, growing hotter by the second. "Screw this waiting around. If we survive this, I swear you will have my full attention from now on."  Her eyes flashed, and I released the hold on my true self, letting Cobalt surge to the surface. My wings unfurled, brushing the countertop, and my talons clicked on the tile floor as I sank down and made myself small, folding my wings tight to my body', 317, 0), (222088, 'Wanna know the secret to nailing a great speech? It''s simple--don''t trust words.', 39624, 0), (222089, 'Ember was watching me, green bright eyes in the shadows of the room. She crouched against the wall with her wings pressed close and her tail curled around herself. Even with her fangs slightly bared and her sides heaving with fear, she was still beautiful, elegant, fiery, everything my dragon wanted.', 317, 0), (222090, 'If it had been a color, it might have been green. If it had touched her ears, it might have sounded rhythmic, like the creak of a rocking chair or drone of a bee. If it had a scent, it might have been sweet and drowsy, like fresh pine on the fire.', 604, 0), (222091, 'Riley took a deep breath. "Yeah," he said, nodding. "You''re right. We can''t stop. We can''t let this continue. The organization will do horrible things to their hatchlings and undesirables even if there are no rogues to take the fall. If I don''t keep fighting Talon, who will?  "I will," I said softly.  He chuckled. "I don''t know, Firebrand. Think you can handle a dozen hormonal teenage dragons if I go down someday?  " I lived with an obnoxious twin brother for years," I responded. " I think I could manage." He arched a dubious eyebrow, and I sobered. " But that''s not going to happen, Riley, because you''re not going to die. This work, what your doing now, is too important. Someone has to stand against Talon, to show our kind what the organization is really like. And your not the only one who has a chance." I raised my chin, my voice firm. " You can''t let them win. We can''t let them win. And I''m going to do whatever it takes for us to succeed." Riley was motionless, watching me with gold eyes, and I held his stare. " I''m not walking away from this," I told him. " Or you. I''ll keep fighting, however long it takes.', 317, 0), (222092, 'This typewriter is the only one that has listened to me throughout the years, the only one who wants to know the girl beneath my layers.', 22939, 0), (222093, 'Ember was mine. The other half of me. And I would fight Talon, St George, and the entire d world to keep her safe.', 317, 0), (222094, 'I know you’re scared. I’m scared too, all of the time. But I have been running for the last six years and I can’t run anymore. Our world is falling apart. We aren’t living, not really. We are just… surviving.', 15433, 0), (222095, 'Rin thought of the crossbow bolt. Of the whoosh and sting of wind and fire heat and the man who would have killed her. Of pushing in front of Enna. Of almost dying. Of home and Ma and being farther away than the lands in tales, and maybe never going home. Of standing by a strange tree in a faraway wood with girls who spoke the language of fire. Of a queen of Kel who wanted them dead.', 604, 0), (222096, 'The only thing that restricted us from becoming one was our MINDS!', 12721, 0), (222097, 'It didn''t matter what anyone else saw in me. For the first time, I felt like I was seeing myself.', 20002, 0), (222098, 'I chose to spend the day with you. And I''m choosing now to have dinner with you.', 20002, 0), (222099, 'No, I''m not one of those guys. I''d never get anything done if I rescued everyone who needed it. But I do like to help people I care about. That''s why I''m here with you right now.', 20002, 0), (222100, 'I had a whole evening planned. I was hoping to sweep you off your feet. Like those guys in your stupid books.', 20002, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (222101, 'I''m so sorry about all you''re going through, but I''m not sorry that it brought you to me.', 20002, 0), (222102, 'Growing up and seeing your parents'' flaws is like losing your religion. I don''t believe in God anymore. I don''t believe in my father either.', 470, 0), (222103, 'I kiss him to get him to stop talking. If he keeps talking I will love him, and I don''t want to love him. I really don''t. As strategies go, it''s not my finest. Kissing is just another way of talking except without the words.', 470, 0), (222104, 'From my bedroom window, I can see the sun peeping through the clouds. London certainly isn''t a city noted for its climate, but I think, sooner or later, you get used to it, and live with the weather. For most of the year, everyone and everything seems to be tucked up cosily in grey cotton wool, but Dickens said that fog is a characteristic of London, didn''t he? This climate could go hand in hand with my dismal humour.', 39625, 0), (222105, 'A strange, beautiful new world awaits, Leonard.We''ve found an oasis in their ruins. We really have.You want to see it, so just hold on, okay?', 607, 0), (222106, 'I don’t know. I guess I’d just like to see you live one day for yourself.', 14103, 0), (222107, 'It’s like I became so obsessed with doing things right, I forgot to enjoy them.', 14103, 0), (222108, 'This is what they mean by epiphanies. I am almost thinking in exclamation points.', 24448, 0), (222109, 'There are so many unknowns, and so many possibilities. Sometimes there are things you can say, and talking makes it better. But sometimes, there are no words.', 7748, 0), (222110, 'I’m so tired of crying.I’m so tired of losing.I’m just so tired.', 14103, 0), (222111, 'When I look at my bookcase and see one book after the other lined up upon its shelves I think to myself, There is a God.', 14111, 0), (222112, 'She was born of space. And starlight. But she bled wrath. And vengeance.."[From Current Work In Progress]', 39626, 0), (222113, 'An uneventful, quiet life together is more my idea of a romance.”“Really? Oh. Well. It won''t get you featured in any of the ballads though.”“Yes,” he said, with a heavy sigh. “And that will be the great tragedy of my romance.', 17305, 0), (222114, 'He was telling war stories. The funny, innocuous ones that made everyone forget that war could leave you without fingers, or legs, or a soul.', 39627, 0), (222115, 'I can’t help to feel like they’re staring at me, too. Judging me. Deeming me not good enough. Not pretty enough. Not cool enough.And to be honest, sometimes I wonder if they’re right.', 14103, 0), (222116, 'The thing that hurts the most, that makes it hard to sleep at night, is not being with you" -Jess Tyler', 14547, 0), (222117, 'Before you say it, Derek''s boyfriend doesn''t look anything like me. ""How would you know?', 13110, 0), (222118, 'Cross my heart, it''s the truth. My Ma consulted a Seer when I was born. He''s fated to marry a girl that wears that ring, she said.” “Did she now?” I said. “Well, this is in mad fashion in Mahmonir, so, prepare yourself, you''re going to be overburdened with wives once the word gets around!', 17305, 0), (222119, 'My dad believes that bad disguises itself - that danger hides. I think it''s the opposite. The truly horrible things about the world are always reaching out for you.', 21327, 0), (222120, 'But there’s nothing.My life is one big meaningless cycle of nothingness.', 14103, 0), (222121, 'And why did he have to call me “quiet”? I hated being called quiet. People always said it like it was some kind of deficiency—like just because I didn’t put everything out there right away, I was unfriendly or arrogant. My mom had understood. You may be slow to warm up, but once you do, you light up the whole room', 13290, 0), (222122, 'That''s the thing about distance: It either gives you time to move on form someone, or it makes you realize just how much you need them.', 39628, 0), (222123, 'You''ve got nothing to be worried about," he whispers slowly, his breath hot against my cheek, "because, baby, I''m all yours.', 39628, 0), (222124, 'I don''t know what being in love with someone is supposed to feel like," Tyler admits with a breathy laugh, "but if being in love means thinking about someone every second of every day... If being in love means your entire mood shifts when they''re around... If being in love means you''d do anything and everything for them," he murmurs, "then I am endlessly in love with you.', 39628, 0), (222125, 'Is there a difference between loving someone and being in love with someone?', 39628, 0), (222126, 'The truth is, we are never just one thing. We all have many titles and many labels, but far too often, we get trapped inside a single definition. The Teacher''s Pet, the Rule Follower, the Cheerleader, the Athlete, the Princess, the Basket Case, the Criminal... the Rock Star''s Girlfriend. Whether we wrote that definition or it was given to us, it somehow becomes our only identity. We get so lost in it that we forget about all the other pieces that make up who we are.', 14103, 0), (222127, 'Dark haired guys are so, so much better.', 39628, 0), (222128, 'It''s gonna take me a lot longer than a year without you to get over you.', 39628, 0), (222129, 'I need you because I''m in love with you, Eden, and I have no idea how I''ll ever get over you.', 39628, 0), (222130, 'I lovehow grown childrenwill still nametheir mothersthe mostbeautiful.It isas though,their eyeshave met the cascadingcurvesand goldensilhouettesof every woman.Yettheir soulsstilldrumto the beat  of theirmother''swarmth and care.', 18333, 0), (222131, 'That''s the thing about distance: It either gives you time to move on from someone, or it makes you realize just how much you need them.', 39628, 0), (222132, 'It was supposed to be us against the world, Tyler and me versus everyone else. Now it''s just me.', 39628, 0), (222133, 'We promised we''d all stay in touch. Even joked about a yearly reunion. These kinds of goodbyes are the scary goodbyes. The goodbyes where you know the chances of seeing each other again are very slim.', 39628, 0), (222134, 'While there are memories I wish I could dispose of, sometimes my memories are the only things that keep me sane.', 921, 0), (222135, 'I think parks like these are the best places to people-watch. The diversity of people here is really cool and, again I find myself wondering what they''re doing and why they''re here and who they''re with. I''m far too curious for my own good.', 39628, 0), (222136, 'No", she said, "I know that you don''t like me.""You don''t know anything.', 54, 0), (222137, 'Cath liked Levi. A lot. She liked looking at him. She liked listening to him -- though sometimes she hated listening to him talk to other people. She hated the way he passed out smiles to everyone he met like it didn''t cost him anything, like he''d never run out. He made everything look so easy.', 54, 0), (222138, 'This is why I can''t be with Levi. Because I''m the kind of girl who fantasizes about being trapped in a library overnight -- and Levi can''t even read.', 54, 0), (222139, 'Every town has its stories. Stories that have been told so many times by so many different people they''ve worked themselves into the collective consciousness as truth.', 8112, 0), (222140, 'The bent but unbroken ones.', 923, 0), (222141, 'When you live in LA and work in the movies, you experience the collapse of some of that fantasy. You know that the eyes glow like that because of lights placed at a specific angle, and you see the actresses up close and, yes, they are beautiful, but they are human size and imperfect like the rest of us.', 351, 0), (222142, 'So you can be ''fantastic'' or ''elastic'' but can you ever be both lol??', 39629, 0), (222143, 'Let''s be honest-we''re a pretty intense bunch, yeah? Osten laughed, and Kaden''s expression brightend. "But whatever we put her through, it was 